# QuickSite — SaaS CMS Platform Architecture

Multi-tenant website builder. Next.js 15 App Router + Prisma + PostgreSQL + Tailwind + Resend.

## Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|-----------|
| Framework | Next.js 15 (App Router, Server Components) |
| Database | PostgreSQL (Neon) via Prisma ORM |
| Auth | Custom sessions — bcrypt + HMAC-SHA256 tokens + httpOnly cookies |
| Email | Resend (`lib/email.ts`) |
| Styling | Tailwind CSS — Ocean design system (`#635BFF`) |
| Icons | Lucide React (never Material Symbols) |
| Validation | Zod |
| Language | Hebrew RTL (`dir="rtl"`) |

## Core Principles

1. **Server-First** — Pages are Server Components. Data fetched at server level. No `useEffect` for data loading.
2. **Client components only for interactivity** — Forms, modals, drag-and-drop. Receive data via props from parent Server Component.
3. **Hebrew RTL** — All UI is `dir="rtl"`. Use `font-noto` for headings, `font-sans` for body.
4. **Email on events** — Every significant user action triggers an email via `lib/email.ts`. Fire-and-forget with `.catch(console.error)`.

## Multi-Tenancy

- Middleware resolves tenant from Host header (`x-tenant-slug` / `x-tenant-host`)
- Platform host = auth pages + dashboard
- Tenant host = public site (rewritten to `/site/...`)
- TenantId always from `user.memberships[0].tenantId` in dashboard

## Auth Flow

- Custom auth in `lib/auth.ts` — no NextAuth/Supabase/Clerk
- `createSession(userId)` → random token → HMAC hashed → DB + httpOnly cookie (`saas_session`)
- `getCurrentUser()` / `getSession()` — cached per-request via React `cache()`
- `destroySession()` — deletes session from DB + clears cookie
- Password reset: `PasswordReset` model with hashed tokens, 60-min expiry, single-use

## Data Flow

```
// ✅ Server Component fetches → Client Component interacts
export default async function Page() {
  const data = await prisma.xxx.findMany({ where: { tenantId } });
  return <ClientForm data={data} />;
}

// ❌ NEVER — Client Component fetches on mount
'use client'
useEffect(() => { fetchData().then(setData) }, []);
```

## After Mutations

Server actions call `revalidatePath()` — page auto-refreshes. For redirects use `redirect()`.

## Key Directories

```
app/(auth)/          — login, register, forgot-password, reset-password
app/dashboard/       — admin panel (protected by layout auth check)
app/site/            — public tenant site (resolved via middleware)
app/onboarding/      — post-registration wizard
lib/auth.ts          — session management
lib/email.ts         — all email functions (Resend)
lib/prisma.ts        — Prisma client singleton
lib/templates.ts     — site templates for registration
components/dashboard/ — dashboard UI components
components/tenant/   — public site block components
```
